President Biden had a phone conversation with President Zelenskyy of Ukraine, where he reaffirmed the United States' readiness to respond decisively if Russia invades Ukraine. He emphasized the US commitment to Ukraine's sovereignty and territorial integrity and mentioned the assistance provided to Ukraine in the past year. President Biden also expressed support for conflict resolution efforts and discussed coordinated diplomatic efforts on European security. He hoped that the recommitment to the ceasefire would help decrease tensions and advance the implementation of the Minsk Agreements.